Dissolutions Descriptives

Percent experienced a dissolution by country

Note: Dissolution includes all relationships longer than 3 years that ended in a breakup (includes divorces)

Percent experienced a dissolution by country and social mobility

Notes: Social mobility is a categorical variable.

  1. Upward: destination class (R’s class) is higher than origin class (father’s class when R was 15)
  2. Static: destination is the same as origin
  3. Downward: destination class is lower than origin class

Percent experienced a dissolution by gender and social mobility

Percent experienced a dissolution by country and cohort

Note: Cohort is a categorical variable

  1. Pre ’65: Born before 1965
  2. Post ’65: Born in 1965 or after.
